## 2.  C++ helper – `pcapng_wrapper.hpp`

Only a **few** lines are needed to expose the relevant parts of the (fictional) C++ library in a C‑compatible way.  
You will have to adapt the includes and the class/namespace names to the real `libpcapng` you are using.

```cpp
/* --------------------------------------------------------------
   pcapng_wrapper.hpp – thin C++ façade for libpcapng
   -------------------------------------------------------------- */

#ifndef PCAPNG_WRAPPER_HPP
#define PCAPNG_WRAPPER_HPP

#include <cstdint>
#include <vector>
#include <memory>
#include <stdexcept>
#include <string>

/* -----------------------------------------------------------------
   The real libpcapng API is not defined here – replace the
   following dummy definitions with the real ones.
   ----------------------------------------------------------------- */

namespace libpcapng {

struct Frame {
    std::int64_t ts_sec;   // seconds part of timestamp
    std::int64_t ts_usec;  // micro‑seconds part
    std::uint32_t caplen;  // captured length
    std::uint32_t origlen; // original length
    std::vector<std::uint8_t> data; // payload (size == caplen)
};

class Reader {
public:
    explicit Reader(const std::string& filename);
    ~Reader();

    // Return a vector of all frames – the real library may give you
    // an iterator, a callback API, etc.  The wrapper turns it into a
    // simple forward iterator.
    class iterator {
        // implementation detail – not part of the public API
    public:
        using iterator_category = std::input_iterator_tag;
        using value_type        = Frame;
        using difference_type   = std::ptrdiff_t;
        using pointer           = const Frame*;
        using reference         = const Frame&;

        iterator();
        iterator(const iterator&);
        iterator& operator=(const iterator&);
        ~iterator();

        reference operator*() const;
        pointer   operator->() const;
        iterator& operator++();        // pre‑increment
        iterator  operator++(int);    // post‑increment
        bool      operator==(const iterator&) const;
        bool      operator!=(const iterator&) const;
    };

    iterator begin() const;
    iterator end()   const;
};

} // namespace libpcapng

/* --------------------------------------------------------------
   Public wrapper type used by the OCaml stubs.
   -------------------------------------------------------------- */

struct pcapng_handle {
    std::unique_ptr<libpcapng::Reader> reader;   // owns the C++ object
    explicit pcapng_handle(const std::string& fn)
        : reader(std::make_unique<libpcapng::Reader>(fn)) {}
};

#endif // PCAPNG_WRAPPER_HPP
```

> **NOTE** – The above file is intentionally minimal.  
> *If the real library already provides a clean C‑API you can skip the wrapper and call it directly from the stubs.*

